<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="124" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="25.[136,1452,1166,2056]" pageId="25" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,490,1778,1804]" pageId="25" pageNumber="124">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
—This species is endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[819,890,1778,1804]" name="Brazil" pageId="25" pageNumber="124">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, in the states of Amazonas, 
<collectingRegion box="[1202,1347,1778,1805]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="25" pageNumber="124">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
and Pará (
<bibRefCitation author="Zuloaga, F. O. &amp; Judziewicz, E. J." box="[144,465,1814,1840]" pageId="25" pageNumber="124" pagination="928 - 941" refId="ref27951" refString="Zuloaga, F. O. &amp; Judziewicz, E. J. (1991) A Revision of Raddiella (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Olyreae). Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 78 (4): 928 - 941." type="journal article" year="1991">Zuloaga &amp; Judziewicz 1991</bibRefCitation>
, Oliveira &amp; Oliveira 2020). In the Serra do Cachimbo, it was found in 
<taxonomicName box="[1270,1451,1815,1841]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Campo" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="25" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rupestre">
<emphasis box="[1270,1451,1815,1841]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="124">Campo rupestre</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
near the borders of 
<collectingRegion box="[354,499,1850,1877]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="25" pageNumber="124">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
and Pará States (
<bibRefCitation author="Zuloaga, F. O. &amp; Judziewicz, E. J." box="[692,1013,1850,1876]" pageId="25" pageNumber="124" pagination="928 - 941" refId="ref27951" refString="Zuloaga, F. O. &amp; Judziewicz, E. J. (1991) A Revision of Raddiella (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Olyreae). Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 78 (4): 928 - 941." type="journal article" year="1991">Zuloaga &amp; Judziewicz 1991</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="124" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[136,1452,1166,2056]" pageId="25" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,1886,1912]" pageId="25" pageNumber="124">Comments:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[356,560,1886,1912]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Raddiella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="25" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis box="[356,560,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="124">Raddiella minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the smallest bamboos of the world (Zuloaga &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Judziewicz, E. J. &amp; Clark, L. G." box="[1252,1447,1886,1912]" pageId="25" pageNumber="124" pagination="80 - 99" refId="ref24854" refString="Judziewicz, E. J. &amp; Clark, L. G. (1993) The South American Species of Arthrostylidium (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Bambuseae). Systematic Botany 18 (1): 80 - 99. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2419790" type="journal article" year="1993">Judziewicz 1993</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Judziewicz, E. J. &amp; Sepsenwol, S." box="[136,492,1922,1948]" pageId="25" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref24905" refString="Judziewicz, E. J. &amp; Sepsenwol, S. (2007) The world's smallest bamboo: Raddiella vanessiae (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Olyreae), a new species from French Guiana. Journal of the Botanical Research Institute of Texas 1 (1): 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="2007">Judziewicz &amp; Sepsenwol 2007</bibRefCitation>
), with filiform culms 
<quantity box="[745,830,1922,1949]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="124" unit="cm" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3–6 cm</quantity>
long, ovate-triangular leaves, asymmetrical, glabrous, base truncate and apex acute to apiculate. It can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. E. Calderon &amp; Soderstrom" authorityYear="1980" baseAuthorityName="Steudel" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[965,1116,1958,1984]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Raddiella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="25" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="esenbeckii">
<emphasis box="[965,1116,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="124">R. esenbeckii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shorter culms, blades 
<quantity box="[136,264,1994,2021]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="124" unit="cm" value="0.5" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.6 cm</quantity>
long, the axillary synflorescences bearing only female spikelets and ovoid-globose caryopsis, with the hilum punctiform, central.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
